Thirteen people were killed when a river ferry sank in western Bangladesh Tuesday, local media reported. The boat carrying some 40 Bangladeshi Hindus returning from a pilgrimage in a neighbouring Indian district sank in the Mohananda river, Channel-I television network reported. The station said nine bodies had been recovered by rescue workers in frontier Chapai Nawabganj district, 235 kilometers (145 miles) west of Dhaka. Local officials were not available immediately for comment. gt/th Bangladesh-ferry 